Suspect of Boston bombings captured in MIT shooting: media
2013-04-19 07:33:26 GMT
BOSTON, the United States, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A suspect of the Boston Marathon bombings was captured early Friday, with a police officer killed in the manhunt, the Boston Globe reported.The suspect was caught in Watertown near the U.S. city of Boston after a police officer was shot dead on the campus of the elite Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), according to the newspaper.Gunfire and blasts were reported in streets near the MIT as the police are still chasing a second suspect.It cannot be immediately confirmed whether the MIT shooting is related to the Boston bombings, which killed three people and injured over 170 on Monday.
